ng blues</span><hr size=1> Caith, 39<br>
Stealth 29 (35 w/ items)<br>
CS 34<br>
Blades 25 (27 w/ items)<br>
Envenom 19 (23 w/ items)<br>
<br>
Haven't done too much of a variety... But against Pookhas (A relatively ideal mob) I've had incredible success since the patch.  Using 2 crescent reavers, lesser enervating on right hand greater lethal on off hand.<br>
Three examples.<br>
1.  Against a yellow Hit perf chain, garrote + achilles to death.  I'm maybe at 75%.<br>
2.  Again, a yellow.  Miss my perf chain.  Garrotte + Achilles it to death... 90% left.  I was utterly shocked after this fight<br>
3.  A blue.  Landed my chain, at which point his yellow friend joined in.  Garrotte and achilles the blue to death, with maybe 30% stam left, and 85% health.  Burn my last endurance on the yellow (Which brings health to even with the Pookha) and melee it down without styles.  Win with a sliver left.  Obviously this is not going to happen often, but I survived a yellow + a blue.<br>
<br>
Right now, I'd quite honestly be comfortable going up to most yellow mobs in Hib and attempting to solo them.<br>
<br>
The blue in the third example probably lasted around 10 seconds against me.<br>
<br>
The biggest obstacle to soloing for us, in my opinion, is setup time.  The degree of effort and time it takes to open with a PA, especially in an area with aggro mobs, makes it very time inefficient.  Tomorrow I may try soloing Pookhas using only poisons and spell to pull, and see how it works.<br>
<br>
In general, I am much happier with our ability to solo (win wise) but am still disappointed at the sheer inefficiency of it (and the inefficiency is independant of con colour.  If there're aggro mobs in the area, we either have to be incredibly careful, or just give up, because sooner or later we'll get an add or two that we can't handle, and die).<br>
